verses.roman:
mukhya mukhya śākhā-gaṇera nāma agaṇana
āge ta' kariba, śuna vṛkṣera varṇana

synonyms: mukhya mukhya—the foremost of them all; śākhā-gaṇera—of the branches; nāma—name; agaṇana—uncountable; āge—subsequently; ta' kariba—I shall do; śuna—please hear; vṛkṣera varṇana—the description of the Caitanya tree.
translation: I shall try to name the foremost of the innumerable branches. Please hear the description of the Caitanya tree.
